Arundinaria pusilla

    Authority   A. Che.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3458

   Notes
   SOURCES (A. pusilla A. Chevalier & A. Camus)
   Mannetje L 1992 pp 50-51 [TEMP, LIG, DRA, PH]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 416 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 7 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial bamboo. In Thailand, it flowers in February and March. (GMIN
   estimated by the compiler).
   COMMON NAMES
   Bamboo grass, Utod, Russei preich, Ph'ek, Ya-phek, Ya-phet, Le, Truc
   th'ao.
   FURTHER INF
   Bamboo grass is most common in South-East Africa between latitudes
   13-17Â°S. It is well adapted to warm environments with a short wet and a
   long dry season. It can be found at elevations between sea level and
   1500 m.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
